1
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:42,520
<i>This is brutal.</i>

2
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:46,720
Praphop is in a coma.

3
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:48,840
<i>At least it confirms our theory.</i>

4
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:51,400
<i>Someone really used</i>
<i>this housekeeper to set you up.</i>

5
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:53,920
<i>And they also went as far</i>
<i>as sending someone to silence her.</i>

6
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,960
They must be really careful
to stay hidden from us.

7
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:59,160
In that case, we need to find her fast.

8
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:01,600
<i>We have evidence, CCTV footage.</i>

9
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:05,520
<i>It clearly shows the last person</i>
<i>with Mr. Praphop was you.</i>

10
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,640
<i>If you ever fall,</i>

11
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:09,600
<i>I'll sit right by your side,</i>

12
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:11,720
<i>until you're back on your feet.</i>

13
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:13,760
Hey!

14
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,080
Who sent you?

15
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,480
Help!

16
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:34,120
Mr. Din!

17
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,960
He'll be awake in no time.

18
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:04,280
And then we'll soon know
who had the audacity to do this to him.

19
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:07,480
That day will never come.

20
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:13,200
Don't try to comfort me.

21
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,360
Why?

22
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:21,160
The doctor said
if his condition stays like this,

23
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:22,880
he'll stay

24
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:27,080
in a coma forever.

25
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,960
I believe miracles happen.

26
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:37,440
You never know.

27
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:40,120
He might wake up in a few days.

28
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:48,480
Then I'll excuse myself
and head back to work.

29
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:58,560
ICU
NO ENTRY WITHOUT PERMISSION

30
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:05,760
<i>That old man and Din,</i>
<i>they're too damn lucky.</i>

31
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:11,480
I don't think you should leave yet.

32
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:15,320
You should rest first. If something
happens on the way, it'll be a mess.

33
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,440
Take this medicine to Mr. Pathawee.

34
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:37,240
What medicine?

35
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:38,840
An antihistamine.

36
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:42,120
Mr. Praphop just had someone
buy it for him.

37
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:47,320
I can't. I don't know what that is.
Please give it to him yourself.

38
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,920
Wait.

39
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:53,600
Give it to him. If you do what I say,

40
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,760
I'll give you 100,000 baht.

41
00:04:58,320 --> 00:05:00,240
A hundred thousand.

42
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:03,600
Once you get the money, you can resign.

43
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,880
And I promise

44
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:08,080
this will never come back to you.

45
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,680
One hundred thousand, right?

46
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:15,880
Cash.

47
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,120
Alright.

48
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:27,680
Mr. Pathawee, please
take some allergy medicine.

49
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,960
- Thank you so much.
- Yes, sir.

50
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:03,040
Din?

51
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:15,000
You're not planning
to discard me like this, are you?

52
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,280
What are you talking about?

53
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,520
You know

54
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,400
how much I sacrificed

55
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:26,000
to take PD away from Din.

56
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,000
Yet you're still taking PD from me.

57
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:32,000
And now you're backing him up too.

58
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,000
Isn't that a bit heartless?

59
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:39,320
In business, there's
no such thing as "heartless."

60
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,240
You know that.

61
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:44,560
There are only winners and losers.

62
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:49,720
So you're saying I'm the loser,

63
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,600
and he

64
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:54,680
is the winner?

65
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:57,240
That's for you to decide.

66
00:06:57,320 --> 00:07:00,920
I simply choose the person
who works best for me.

67
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,560
You still have your strengths.

68
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:08,000
But if you cause trouble,
I can fire you right now.

69
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:15,480
So, in the end,

70
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:19,400
I'm just another pawn to you, aren't I?

71
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:22,040
Well, now you know.

72
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:25,240
Then start acting like one.

73
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,800
Ouch, Chakrit!

74
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:37,280
If you're going to do this,
make sure I die.

75
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:39,360
If I survive,

76
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:41,440
I'll make you suffer worse than death.

77
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,520
Try to survive, Din.

78
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,480
How the hell is he breathing again?

79
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,400
Thank you, Mom.

80
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:23,880
For using all your land deeds
to bail me out.

81
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:28,120
I helped because I know
you'd never hurt anyone.

82
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:34,920
Come on, Mom. If you want
to help Din, just admit it.

83
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:36,760
Be quiet.

84
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:39,080
This is all I can do.

85
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:41,360
From now, you'll have to figure
things out yourself.

86
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,920
Yes, Mom.

87
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:50,600
Alright.

88
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:53,240
And don't go causing more trouble.

89
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:57,400
If your bail gets revoked and you end up
in jail, I won't be able to help anymore.

90
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:02,640
So, what are you gonna do next, Din?

91
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:05,200
The police have all this CCTV footage.

92
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,280
Even with the footage,

93
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,200
it doesn't prove

94
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,680
Mr. Din harmed Mr. Praphop.

95
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:16,960
Don't worry.

96
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:20,160
I'll fight this to the very end.

97
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:41,400
Mr. Chakrit.

98
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:44,920
Ms. Rosarin has been waiting
to see you for quite a while now.

99
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,360
Did you ask what it's about?

100
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:49,800
She didn't say.

101
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:10,200
Ms. Rosarin, if you were coming,
why didn't you tell me first?

102
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:12,680
I would've come right away.
Sorry to keep you waiting.

103
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,480
It's alright.

104
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:19,240
I just wanted to talk to you
about a few things.

105
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:21,520
Nothing too serious.

106
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:24,160
Then please go ahead.

107
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:28,320
Why did you suspend the capital increase?

108
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:30,960
You already know

109
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,520
what Mr. Praphop wants, don't you?

110
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,520
Nothing too serious, huh?

111
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:40,040
Anything I can handle,

112
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:42,560
I consider a small matter.

113
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,320
There's nothing.

114
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:49,600
I only wanted Mr. Praphop
to recover first before moving forward.

115
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:53,200
After all, he was the one
who initiated this project.

116
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:56,560
I wanted him to be aware of every step.

117
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:59,080
And I was worried
something might go wrong.

118
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,320
I believe you.

119
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:18,520
But don't worry.

120
00:13:19,040 --> 00:13:21,880
He regained consciousness last night.

121
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:35,720
I'm glad to hear that.

122
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:41,440
Now that you know,

123
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,720
you should cancel your order as well.

124
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:47,440
- But…
- Sorry.

125
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:50,600
Handling everything alone
might be too much,

126
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:52,480
so I found someone to help you.

127
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:56,080
That way, everything will run smoothly,

128
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,840
just as Mr. Praphop wants.

129
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,520
Who is it?

130
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:04,560
You'll see soon enough.

131
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:08,400
But I don't think this is the right time
to bring in an outsider.

132
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,840
Even though Mr. Praphop
has regained consciousness,

133
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,440
- but--
- Not an outsider.

134
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:16,280
But someone who's been
with this company from the start.

135
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:21,120
Why bring back someone
who assaulted Mr. Praphop?

136
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:23,760
The police granted him bail

137
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,520
until the case is concluded.

138
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:30,120
Until then, I consider Din innocent.

139
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:33,520
And if it turns out Din really did it?

140
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,080
Really wish it were me, don't you?

141
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,320
Have you forgotten

142
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:41,680
who stands to lose the most
if there's a capital increase?

143
00:14:41,760 --> 00:14:43,320
Don't stir things up, Din.

144
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:44,920
You hold shares too.

145
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,560
If there's a capital increase,
you'd take a hit as well.

146
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:49,160
So why couldn't you have hurt him?

147
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:51,320
Because Mr. Din doesn't crave power.

148
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,200
All this time,

149
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,920
whenever something benefited PD,

150
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,280
he never hesitated to do it.

151
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:02,040
So why would he hurt Mr. Praphop?

152
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,160
I think

153
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:09,680
Ms. Rosarin should be the one to decide.

154
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:13,320
Good.

155
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:15,640
I've already decided.

156
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:17,680
That's why I'm bringing Din back.

157
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:20,960
There's no need
to go back and forth on this.

158
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:37,280
Thank you so much, Auntie, for helping me.

159
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,120
It's fine.

160
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:44,080
Consider this another chance from me

161
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:46,080
for you to prove your innocence.

162
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:50,760
But don't forget to keep your promise.

163
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:53,960
Yes.

164
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:56,280
<i>You still have the nerve</i>
<i>to ask for my help</i>

165
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:59,920
while my husband is lying in the ICU?

166
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,640
Where does that confidence come from?

167
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,600
My confidence

168
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,880
comes from the fact
that I didn't hurt him.

169
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:12,960
Isn't the CCTV footage enough?

170
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:19,800
But there isn't a single clip
showing him attacking Mr. Praphop.

171
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:24,000
What we can say for now is…

172
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:28,880
Mr. Din may have been
the last person with him.

173
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:30,680
But its only maybe.

174
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,040
There are still suspicious gaps.

175
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:36,720
Like what?

176
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,800
I was drugged.

177
00:16:40,920 --> 00:16:42,680
Not allergy medicine,

178
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:47,160
but a strong sleeping pill. Otherwise,
I wouldn't have blacked out like that.

179
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:52,600
And the person who drugged Mr. Din
was silenced as well.

180
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:57,680
Mr. Nam can testify to this.
If you don't believe us,

181
00:16:57,760 --> 00:17:01,760
you can call Mr. Nam yourself
or check with the police.

182
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:04,160
We've already provided
all the information.

183
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:05,920
Alright.

184
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:11,480
I'll verify how credible this is.

185
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:16,200
Does that mean you're willing to help me?

186
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:24,680
Why do you want to return to PD?

187
00:17:25,359 --> 00:17:26,560
Because I'm certain

188
00:17:28,119 --> 00:17:29,960
the real culprit is still there.

189
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:32,840
Chakrit?

190
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:38,800
If we're talking about motive,

191
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:40,440
Mr. Chakrit

192
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:43,280
is someone we can't rule out, isn't he?

193
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:49,800
Alright.

194
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,200
I agree.

195
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:55,440
- Thank you so much--
- Not yet.

196
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:57,160
I'm not helping for free.

197
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:03,760
All the PD shares you currently hold…

198
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:06,840
If you sell them to me, I'll help.

199
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:10,320
But don't worry.

200
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,120
I won't undercut the price.

201
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,840
I've already had my lawyer
draft the share purchase agreement.

202
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:23,960
I'll tell you once it's ready.

203
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,600
Alright.

204
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:41,800
You've fought this hard for PD.

205
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:45,200
Why give in so easily?

206
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:49,520
I don't want to take the fall
for something I didn't do.

207
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:54,400
And I want to bring
the real culprit to justice.

208
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:58,200
Don't you regret it?

209
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:04,160
If I said I didn't, I'd be lying.

210
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:12,160
But uncovering the truth

211
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:15,200
and your peace of mind

212
00:19:15,840 --> 00:19:17,440
matter more to me.

213
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:36,920
Make sure I die. If I survive,

214
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:40,240
I'll make you suffer worse than death.

215
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:12,520
If I hadn't already known
something was going on,

216
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:15,040
I'd really need to reflect on myself
as the shop owner.

217
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:17,640
If customers won't eat it,

218
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:19,600
then something must be wrong
with the food.

219
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:30,840
Sorry about that.
We've all been a bit stressed.

220
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:33,840
It tastes just as good as ever.

221
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,520
Come on. Don't stress.

222
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:40,920
I was just teasing.

223
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,080
So, how far have you gotten?

224
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:47,320
We need more evidence.

225
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,400
We're still figuring out what to do next.

226
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:51,440
The key witness has fled.

227
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:56,560
We don't even know
where to track down Aunt Noi right now.

228
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:00,160
But oddly enough,
I'm not worried about that.

229
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:05,240
Because I have Uncle Perm.

230
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:09,800
And I'm sure he'll find her
sooner or later.

231
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:12,720
What I am worried about

232
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:14,880
is tonight's plan.

233
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:17,640
Afraid it won't go as planned?

234
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:19,760
No.

235
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,960
I'm afraid he won't show up.

236
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,800
I'll be going home to sleep tonight.

237
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:43,160
Please arrange the private nurse as well.

238
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:45,320
Of course, ma'am.

239
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:06,640
VIP 3102 - MR. PRAPHOP PHAWATNARONGKUL
DR. ANONT SAWASDEE - NO FOOD

240
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:09,080
The car is ready, ma'am

241
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:40,000
VIP 3102 - MR. PRAPHOP PHAWATNARONGKUL
DR. ANONT SAWASDEE - NO FOOD

242
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:54,560
The doctor prescribed
additional medication.

243
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:56,240
Really? No one told me.

244
00:22:56,320 --> 00:22:58,160
You can check with the counter outside.

245
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:24,000
Hey, stop!

246
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:27,640
Hey!

247
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:48,480
Stop!

248
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:50,640
FIRE EXIT

249
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:01,200
Stop! Don't resist!

250
00:24:02,280 --> 00:24:03,440
Freeze!

251
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,440
Take his mask off, Din.

252
00:24:14,360 --> 00:24:17,280
I'm done with this.
If anything happens to Mr. Praphop,

253
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:19,520
I will never forgive any of you.

254
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:22,520
This was risky,
and we gained nothing from it.

255
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:25,040
I take full responsibility.

256
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:30,600
I never thought Chakrit would be
cunning enough to hire someone else.

257
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:33,720
But in another way,

258
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:37,520
this proves Mr. Din was telling the truth.

259
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:39,480
Mr. Din didn't harm him.

260
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:42,120
Someone else was trying to.

261
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:45,480
Fine. I accept that.

262
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:48,920
But

263
00:24:49,680 --> 00:24:52,720
I won't risk my husband's life
like this again.

264
00:24:53,320 --> 00:24:54,600
Do you understand, Din?

265
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:56,280
Yes.

266
00:24:57,240 --> 00:25:00,000
And I think Chakrit,
after making this mistake,

267
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:01,680
won't act recklessly again.

268
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:08,400
Then let's talk business.

269
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:11,360
My lawyer said

270
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:14,240
the share purchase agreement is complete.

271
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,200
Once I've reviewed it,

272
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:19,280
I'll call you in to sign.

273
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:21,360
Alright.

274
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:27,680
Then Sara and I will take our leave.

275
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:50,520
Please.

276
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,520
INQUIRY OFFICER

277
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:56,360
If you need any of my staff
as additional witnesses,

278
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:59,920
just let me know. I'll coordinate with HR.

279
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:01,600
Understood.

280
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:04,800
Ah.

281
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:07,360
Are you alright, Auntie?

282
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:11,120
I'm fine. Could you give me a ride?

283
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:13,360
- I'm feeling dizzy.
- Of course.

284
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:15,400
Right this way, Auntie.

285
00:26:18,640 --> 00:26:20,000
This way, Mr. Chakrit.

286
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:29,360
Mr. Chakrit.

287
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:33,720
Anything to explain about hiring
a housekeeper to drug Mr. Pathawee?

288
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:36,280
I didn't hire her.

289
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:39,800
I only told her to give
Mr. Pathawee his medicine.

290
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:43,520
If she picked up the wrong pills,
how would I know?

291
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:47,080
But we found the money
you paid her for that.

292
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:48,800
And where's the proof, Officer?

293
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:53,120
Listening to just one side,
anyone can say anything.

294
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:56,320
Maybe she took money from someone else

295
00:26:56,840 --> 00:26:58,320
and framed me.

296
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:02,000
Then what about the hitman

297
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:05,000
sent to silence the housekeeper you hired?

298
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:07,920
What do you say to that?

299
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:12,880
The housekeeper we just passed

300
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:14,840
is still alive, isn't she?

301
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:19,640
So, where's this hitman exactly?

302
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:22,600
What evidence do you have
that links this to me?

303
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:25,600
Let me be honest, Officer.

304
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:28,240
Don't you suspect

305
00:27:28,960 --> 00:27:30,680
that Mr. Pathawee might have orchestrated

306
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:33,240
this whole situation himself?

307
00:27:54,280 --> 00:27:56,960
He's unbelievably slippery.

308
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:59,600
Even the police can't corner him.

309
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:19,040
What are you doing?

310
00:28:19,560 --> 00:28:21,400
I'm stressing out right now.

311
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,800
Please let me recharge here.

312
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:26,480
It's truly exhausting this time.

313
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:45,600
Feeling better?

314
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:48,920
Can I have a little more?

315
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:55,360
Okay.

316
00:28:56,560 --> 00:28:58,240
I'll be serious now.

317
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:03,560
Chakrit said he didn't hire anybody.

318
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:06,240
He said he asked the housekeeper
to bring me medicine.

319
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:08,640
So, there's not enough evidence

320
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:10,920
to find out who hurt Uncle Praphop.

321
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,560
And?

322
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:16,040
And Chakrit…

323
00:29:16,720 --> 00:29:18,440
He's a perfectionist.

324
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:21,000
It won't be long

325
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:24,240
before he makes his move.

326
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:54,280
<i>Make sure I die.</i>

327
00:29:54,360 --> 00:29:56,400
If I survive,

328
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:59,320
I'll make you suffer worse than death.

329
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:06,560
There's no way

330
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:09,800
Chakrit can silence Mr. Praphop now.

331
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:11,360
After that day,

332
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:15,320
Ms. Rosarin stationed guards
outside his room.

333
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:18,320
And everyone coming in is checked,

334
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:19,680
even doctors and nurses.

335
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:23,840
That's good. I don't want Krit
to go any further down the wrong path.

336
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:26,440
So that lead is dead then?

337
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:28,360
Looks like it.

338
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:31,560
Right now,

339
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:33,400
the only option left
is fleeing the country

340
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:35,640
before the evidence closes in.

341
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:37,840
There's no better way.

342
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,160
AUNTIE

343
00:30:46,840 --> 00:30:48,040
Auntie's calling.

344
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:50,320
Must be about the shares.

345
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:55,120
Hello, Auntie?

346
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:15,240
SIGNATURE OF TRANSFEROR

347
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:38,920
I know how much PD means to you.

348
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:39,840
MR. PATHAWEE PHIMARNDECH
120 MILLION BAHT

349
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:42,440
Consider the extra money as compensation.

350
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:46,360
Even without shares in the company,

351
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:49,320
you'll remain CEO.

352
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:51,160
Because I know

353
00:31:51,240 --> 00:31:55,600
you can protect PD
and generate profit for me.

354
00:31:58,960 --> 00:31:59,840
Thank you so much.

355
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:07,880
You say you're fine,
but you look miserable.

356
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:10,080
So stubborn.

357
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:18,080
Why are you laughing?
Don't give me that emotional stuff.

358
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:19,600
"I'm worried about you."

359
00:32:19,680 --> 00:32:21,160
That's not it.

360
00:32:22,280 --> 00:32:25,960
I'll tell you everything once we're home.

361
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:30,840
Fine, Mr. Mastermind.
So many secret plans.

362
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:35,120
If you don't tell me at home later,
you're in trouble.

363
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:40,440
I'm going to the restroom,
in case the traffic is bad.

364
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:42,560
Alright. I'll wait here.

365
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:43,640
Yes.

366
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:46,600
Hey.

367
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:50,960
Hey,

368
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:54,840
once we're separated

369
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:56,560
and unable to contact each other,

370
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:59,560
ask the nurse to check
CCTV footage right away, okay?

371
00:33:00,160 --> 00:33:04,040
Is that really necessary?
We'll only be apart for a few minutes.

372
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:06,280
You're being too careful.

373
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:08,360
In a situation like this,

374
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:10,240
there's no such thing as "too careful."

375
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:14,760
Alright.

376
00:33:16,040 --> 00:33:16,920
Okay.

377
00:33:43,680 --> 00:33:45,920
Sorry to startle you.

378
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:47,760
It's alright.

379
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:21,679
What’s taking her so long?

380
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:54,040
You won't escape.

381
00:34:54,679 --> 00:34:57,800
If Mr. Din can't reach me, he'll know

382
00:34:57,880 --> 00:35:00,600
it was your doing.

383
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:03,400
I'm not afraid anymore.
I've got nothing left to lose.

384
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:06,840
So I'll use you as leverage to force Din

385
00:35:06,920 --> 00:35:08,200
to take all the blame.

386
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:11,080
What’s that got to do with me?

387
00:35:11,160 --> 00:35:13,120
Because you're the woman Din loves.

388
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:15,520
If I don't kill you,
who else should I kill?

389
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:18,920
Shut up.

390
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:30,840
Walk properly. Act normal.

391
00:35:48,560 --> 00:35:50,080
Come here.

392
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:07,600
You think you're tough, huh?

393
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:11,960
Come here.

394
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:15,560
Get in.

395
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:19,840
Hands here. Stay still!

396
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:23,720
Don't move. Got it?

397
00:36:27,760 --> 00:36:29,200
Sara.

398
00:36:44,120 --> 00:36:44,960
Come out.

399
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:47,040
Come here.

400
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:49,360
Everyone back off. Or I'll shoot her.

401
00:36:50,080 --> 00:36:53,320
Easy. Easy, Chakrit. I'm backing away.

402
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:54,640
Calm down.

403
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:57,520
She really matters to you, doesn't she?

404
00:36:58,280 --> 00:37:01,000
Listen to me, Chakrit. It's over.

405
00:37:01,080 --> 00:37:03,840
If you could've taken Sara,
I'd have done whatever you wanted.

406
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:06,680
But even if you escape now,
you'll be caught eventually.

407
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:09,920
Then we'll all die right here.

408
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,120
I'm not going to prison.

409
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:24,720
And if I have to die,

410
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:26,280
I'm taking her with me.

411
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:28,560
Let Sara go

412
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,680
and we can talk.

413
00:37:31,200 --> 00:37:33,720
You want to kill me, don't you?
Then do it.

414
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:35,160
No, Mr. Din!

415
00:37:36,040 --> 00:37:37,320
So in love, aren't you?

416
00:37:38,200 --> 00:37:41,240
What's so great about the Phimarndechs?
What's so special, huh?!

417
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:42,600
That's enough, Chakrit.

418
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:46,360
Let Sara go. I'm right here.

419
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:48,600
Do whatever you want to me.
Don't hurt her.

420
00:37:48,680 --> 00:37:50,840
I will! So what?

421
00:37:50,920 --> 00:37:53,760
You can't stand it, can you?
Watching the person you love

422
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:55,960
die right in front of you?
Let me tell you, Din.

423
00:37:56,560 --> 00:37:59,320
If she dies, it's on you.

424
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:01,320
The more you hurt me,

425
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:04,040
the more I'll hurt you, a hundred times,
a thousand times more.

426
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:06,560
I'll make your life a living hell

427
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:08,720
because you can't protect
someone you love.

428
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:13,440
And what about me?

429
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:16,120
Baicha.

430
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:21,480
Did the whole family show up now?

431
00:38:22,560 --> 00:38:23,600
Why are you here?

432
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:26,080
Please, Krit.

433
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:28,560
Don't make this any worse.

434
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:30,760
It can't get any worse than this, Baicha.

435
00:38:30,840 --> 00:38:32,840
Look at my life.

436
00:38:32,920 --> 00:38:35,560
It's completely destroyed.
I have nothing left.

437
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:37,920
And what about me?

438
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:41,800
You said

439
00:38:41,880 --> 00:38:43,920
Din deserves to die inside

440
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:46,800
for failing to protect the one he loves.

441
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:49,760
But have you ever thought

442
00:38:49,840 --> 00:38:52,720
that I'll have to live with the same guilt

443
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:58,240
for not being able to protect
my only brother?

444
00:39:01,480 --> 00:39:02,640
Krit…

445
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:05,480
Please let Ms. Sarah go.

446
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:08,280
I'm begging you.

447
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:11,400
Don't go any further than this.

448
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:23,720
My child still wants to meet their uncle.

449
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:27,920
Still wants you
to carry them on your back,

450
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:33,080
just like you carried me
when we were kids.

451
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,800
I love you, Krit.

452
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:43,960
And my child…

453
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:48,520
will love you too.

454
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:07,880
Sara, are you okay? Are you hurt?

455
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:09,880
No. I'm fine.

456
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:31,880
Baicha…

457
00:40:32,400 --> 00:40:35,160
I'm sorry for everything.

458
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:03,680
What are you all doing here?

459
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:05,200
Get out right now.

460
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:08,360
<i>My parents are now the major shareholders,</i>

461
00:41:09,240 --> 00:41:12,000
<i>so I'll be taking over the company myself.</i>

462
00:41:13,520 --> 00:41:14,440
What's this?

463
00:41:14,520 --> 00:41:15,800
PD GROUP
RESIGNATION LETTER

464
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:17,200
You resigned?

465
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:21,320
Stop being mad at him. Be careful.
If you keep playing hard to get,

466
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:23,520
<i>and one day he gives up on you,</i>

467
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:27,080
<i>don't say I didn't warn you.</i>

468
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:28,160
Mr. Din.

469
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:31,040
Sara?

470
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:17,120
Subtitle translation by: Praeploy Mahawan
